examples.en: Rotavirus is a common cause of gastroenteritis in children.
A vaccine for rotavirus, RotaShield, was pulled off the production in 1999.
Vaccines from measles and rotavirus will also become affordable in developing countries.
Rotavirus killed an average of about 20-50 children a year before vaccines became available.
